    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n3197" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἕννῡμι</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ϝέννῡμι</span>), fut. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἕσσω</span>, aor.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἕσσα</span>, imp. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἕσσον</span>, inf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἕσσαι</span>, part.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἕσσᾱς</span>, mid. and pass., pres. inf.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἕννυσθαι</span>, ipf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἕννυτο</span>, aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἕσ̓σατο,
            ἑέσσατο</span>, inf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἕσασθαι</span>,
          part. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἑσσάμενος</span>, perf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εἷμαι, ἕσσαι, εἷται</span>, part. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εἱμένος</span>, plup. 2 sing. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἕσσο, 3 ἕστο, ἕεστο</span>, du. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἕσθην</span>, 3 pl. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εἵατο</span>:
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">clothe, put on clothing</span>, mid., on oneself, pass.
          (esp. perf. and plup.), <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">be clothed in, wear;</span> act., of
          clothing another, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἕσσᾱς με χλαῖναν τε χιτῶνά
            τε</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 14.396</span></i>; thus
          regularly w. two accusatives, <i><span class="en">Il.
            5.905</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 15.338</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 16.79</span></i>; mid. w. acc., or acc.  and dat., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χροὶ̄ χαλκόν</span>,
            <i><span class="en">Il. 19.233</span></i>; also <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">περὶ χροΐ,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Il. 7.207</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc"> ἀμφ᾽
            ὤμοισιν</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 10.177</span></i>;
          pass. w. acc. of thing retained, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τεύχεα εἱμένος,
            κακὰ εἱμένος, ἀείκεα ἕσσο</span>, ‘shockingly clothed,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 4.432</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od.
            19.327</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 16.199</span></i>; fig.,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἦ τέ κε λά̄ϊνον ἕσσο χιτῶνα</span>, ‘hadst
          been clad in a coat of stone’ (stoned to death), <i><span class="en">Il. 3.57</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; φρεσὶν εἱμένος ἀλκήν</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 20.381</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
